# Second Brain Standards

- **Official system documentation** belongs in **`3-Resources/Second-Brain/Docs/`**. The `Second-Brain` folder is dev docs; `Docs` inside it is the user-facing documentation.
- **PARA** method strictly: 1-Projects (time-bound), 2-Areas (ongoing responsibility), 3-Resources (evergreen reference), 4-Archives (inactive). Never use or reference: 00 Inbox, 10 Zettelkasten, 99 Attachments, 99 Templates. Do not invent new PARA/folder patterns — adhere to mcp-obsidian-integration and Vault-Layout only.
- All notes get searchable title, frontmatter, #tags.
- Atomic notes preferred — split if > 1–2 screens.
- Use `![[5-Attachments/PDFs/...]]` etc. for attachments, `[[ ]]` for note links.
- Note filenames: `kebab-slug-YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM.md` (slug first, date and time at end) per [[3-Resources/Second-Brain/Naming-Conventions|Naming-Conventions]]; daily/ingest date-time when created today.
